</step3>
<step3>
<ptxt>When the power steering link assembly moves during a collision (primary collision), the No. 2 intermediate shaft sub-assembly contracts, thus helping to reduce the amount that the steering column and the steering wheel protrude into the cabin.</ptxt>
</step3>
<step3>
<ptxt>When an impact is transmitted to the steering wheel in a collision (secondary collision), the steering wheel helps absorb the impact. In addition, the breakaway bracket and the lower bracket separate, causing the entire steering column to move forward. At this time, the energy absorbing plate becomes deformed and the steering sliding with coupling yoke sub-assembly contracts to help absorb the impact of the secondary collision.</ptxt>
